File: Zimbabwean journalist Hopewell Chin'ono. JOHANNESBURG - After more than six weeks behind bars, Zimbabwean journalist Hopewell Chin'ono has been granted bail. Chin'ono was arrested in July on charges of inciting public violence. READ: Zimbabwean journalist denied bail for third time Since then he's been denied bail three times. Zimbabwe's been on edge with prominent activists and journalists arrested for protesting alleged corruption.